  // =====================================================================
  //  PIECE 2 — Hardened rules for the AUTOFLAG app ONLY.
  //  Every other app (eats, taskboard, command_center, philinity, foodswipe,
  //  veritas, users, config) is preserved EXACTLY as your current live rules,
  //  so deploying this changes nothing outside autoflag.
  //
  //  >>> DEPLOY ORDER — READ THIS <<<
  //  1. PR #1 (Piece 1, the client) MUST be merged + live on GitHub Pages first.
  //  2. Verify all three roles work in the live app.
  //  3. ONLY THEN paste these rules into the Firebase console and Publish.
  //  Reason: the OLD client (pre-Piece-1) makes customers read the WHOLE
  //  installs/customers node. These rules deny that for customers, so a customer
  //  on the old client would lose their data until Piece 1 is live.
  //
  //  ROLLBACK: paste your previous rules back in the console and Publish (~seconds).
  //
  //  HOW IT WORKS (no Cloud Function, no re-login needed):
  //   - Roles come from the admin-managed roster at autoflag/people/{emailKey}
  //     (emailKey = email lowercased with '.' -> '_', matching the client).
  //   - Two ROOT admin UIDs are always admin (lockout-proof).
  //   - READS are granted at the LEAF, so a customer can only read their own
  //     customer subtree — the database now enforces what the app used to only
  //     hide. (This is what makes the F12 probe return just city_of_boise.)
  //   - WRITES: people is admin-only and now actually ENFORCED (no top-level
  //     grant for installers to override it), so installers can no longer
  //     promote themselves to admin.
  //   - customers_uid self-grant write is disabled; reads no longer depend on
  //     it, so the old self-grant bypass is closed.
  //
  //  KNOWN, INTENTIONAL FOLLOW-UP: issues are still readable by any roster
  //  member (flat data structure). Customer WRITES to issues are scoped to
  //  their own customerId. Full issue read-isolation is the next, separate step.
  // =====================================================================

